title: Syed Ijaz Hussain Bukhari wins PP-3 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent candidate, Syed Ijaz Hussain Bukhari has won the election for Punjab Assembly constituency PP-3, Attock-III by securing 36,897 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Pakistan Muslim League (N) candidate, Hameed Akbar who bagged 31,857 votes.
The votersâ€™ turnout remained 52.89%.
